We would like to thank and honor all of the 2019/20 Moorhead Area Public Schools retirees this summer. Meet Barb!

Teacher Barb Stack is retiring after joining Moorhead Area Public Schools in 1989. â€œI'm leaving education knowing that teaching had the best years of me. I've put myself on the line for what I believe is best for learners and education. As I watch this chapter of life close,
I look back with no regrets,â€ she says.

Her most memorable "time period" in her career includes the years she taught at Robert Asp under the leadership of Dr. Betty Myers. â€œShe created a school culture that was a mystical blend of high expectations, creativity and extended family. My skills as an educator and my growth as a human being grew under her mentorship more that I believed possible. Those years, and Robert Asp, will always hold a special place in my heart.â€

In retirement, Barb looks forward to seeing all of the National Parks in the lower 48 states with her husband.

#SpudPride #OnceASpudAlwaysASpud ðŸ§¡

We would like to thank and honor all of our 2019/20 Moorhead Area Public Schools retirees this summer. Meet Mary!

Teacher Mary Broberg is retiring after joining Moorhead Area Public Schools in 1989.

She has always had a heart for working with at-risk kids. â€œI have tried to foster flexibility and resilience in my students by providing an atmosphere of community and caring. Working on meaningful projects, having structure and high standards for behavior and academics, and advocating for students, without judgement, have always been core to the way I operate,â€ she says.

During her career, Mary has taught students at the Red River Adult Learning Center, Moorhead High School and West Central Regional Juvenile Center.

In retirement, Mary is excited to travel in a motorhome with her husband during the winter and relax at their lake home in the summer. She also plans to read, quilt and entertain... in groups of 10 or less.

post_text:
Effective immediately, Moorhead Area Public Schools are closed until March 30 for the health and safety of our students, staff and community.

We will keep the community up to date with the latest information as it becomes available.

As we navigate COVID-19, we will continue to follow the advice of the state and local experts. The complexity of the decision of closing schools is immense and our leadership team is working diligently to provide additional details as they become available.

post_text: We Are Proud of Moorhead High School wrestlers Evan Fankhanel, Ryan Luthi and Xander Risdal for qualifying for the state tournament at the end of February. Sophomore 120lb wrestler Evan Fankhanel, and senior 145lb wrestler Ryan Luthi were section champions at their weight classes and senior 126lb wrestler Xander Risdal was a runner up, placing second in his weight division. The wrestling team is coached by Gerad Fugleberg.

post_text: We Are Proud of Moorhead High School Senior Kai Holm on his appointment to the U.S. Military Academy at West Point, New York. Representative Collin Peterson made the announcement in a phone call to Holm and his parents, Jeremy and Stacey. Holm is a member of the National Honor Society, an Academic Award Winner and a member of the Key Club. He is a three-sport athlete, participating in hockey, trap shooting and baseball, serving as captain of the Spuds baseball team this year.

post_text: We Are Proud of Moorhead senior Chrisanto D'Agostino, who won a national weightlifting title at the National Junior Championships in Pleasanton, Calif. Dâ€™Agostino took first place for his overall total in the 96 kilograms (212 pounds) weight division. He lifted a combined 291 kilos (642 pounds) between the snatch and clean and jerk. Moorhead weightlifting coach Cory Hermann said Dâ€™Agostino is the first Minnesota lifter to win a National Junior championship. Weightlifting coaches are Cory Herrmann, John Lubitz, Lexi Thomas, Dylan Surface, and Erin Eidelbes.

post_text: February is African American History Month. We celebrate the contributions that African Americans have made to history, recognize the struggles that they have faced along the way and are reminded of the importance of freedom and equality.

post_text: We Are Proud of the Moorhead High School volleyball team for advancing to the state tournament after winning the section title. The volleyball team advanced to the state tournament for the fifth straight year after a win against Brainerd in the Minnesota Class 3A, Section 8 semifinal and a win over Sartell-St. Stephens to take the section championship. Team members are Carleigh Vedder, Claire Howell, Alexa Gronwold, Ayana Blythe, Sam Zimmerman, Megan Haugo, Anna Knain, Ella Swedberg, Riane Mohagen, Willow Carrier, Bryn Stumo, Jalen Ennen, Rosie Anderson, Grace Perry, Mya Pfiefer and student manager Shelby Holman. Head coach is Char Lien, and assistant coaches are Amber Gunkel, Courtney Selbitschka and Kortney Carney. #SpudPride
